    "plan_id": "a27670d4-c585-467b-a496-6cebeccfd274",
    "morning_message": "Good morning, Ameena. You're starting today at 100/100 — that's an exceptional morning feeling.\n\nLast night you got 6.9 hours of sleep with really strong recovery signals: your overnight HRV was up at 110ms and you spent 16% of your sleep in deep stages. That's objectively solid sleep architecture, especially considering yesterday's massive activity day (22,341 steps and 230 minutes of MVPA — that's huge). Your body is clearly adapting well to high loads, which is why you're waking up feeling this energized.\n\nBut there's an interesting disconnect here. Yesterday, you rated your sleep quality at 36/100 — that's a poor subjective rating that reflects the night before last, not last night. And your subjective state yesterday was mixed: mood at 62, energy at 51, with emotions that included both Happy/Alert and Tired/Frustrated. Yet your stress was low (21) and your coping capacity was high (69), with a massive -45 gap between stress and workload. So emotionally you felt some internal conflict, but functionally you were managing it well.\n\nTwo patterns stand out. First, your eating window yesterday was extremely long — over 22 hours, with a snack that included caffeine at midnight. Even with good objective sleep metrics, that timing can affect sleep onset and subjective experience. Second, despite yesterday's moderate mood and energy ratings, your physiological markers are outstanding: daytime HRV at 104ms, oxygen saturation at 96.7%, all suggesting your body is handling everything well.\n\nToday is about protecting that momentum while addressing the few areas that could use refinement. You've got incredible physiological capacity and recovery — now it's about aligning your habits to match how good your body actually is at handling stress and activity.\n\nGiven your high energy and perfect morning score, today's focus is on maintaining that peak state through intentional timing and awareness.\n\nYou've built remarkable physiological resilience — today's about using that foundation to create even more consistency in how you feel.",
